      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It is entirely understandable to feel this way when the effort feels futile, but the \"law of physics\" is simply your brain's way of trying to protect you from failure by predicting it. This isn't a permanent state of being broken; it is a temporary state of exhaustion that you can overcome by changing your approach. You are not stuck in an unfixable loop, but rather in a cycle of trying to fix the same problem without addressing the root cause, which is why the results feel identical.",
